headline: CrowdStrike Stock Drops on Cautious Outlook -- Is This a Buying Opportunity?
summary: CrowdStrike shares fell after its latest results and guidance disappointed investors.  Revenue and ARR continue to show decelerating growth.  Share prices of CrowdStrike (NASDAQ: CRWD) sank after the company reported further deceleration of its revenue growth and maintained its full-year revenue guidance.
